-- World Bank to Fund Mozambican Projects Worth $143 Million, Noticias Says
-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 2010-11-17T04:20:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-17/world-bank-to-fund-mozambican-projects-worth-143-million-noticias-says.html
The World Bank will agree to fund
four projects worth $143 million with the Mozambican government,
the state-controlled daily Noticias reported, citing a
communique from the bank.  The funding will be in health and water supply and
implemented throughout the country, the Maputo-based newspaper
reported today.   Planning and Development Minister Aiuba Cuereneia will sign
the agreement with representatives from the World Bank,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
